COPS have found the hijacked car that had a one-month-old baby inside when the hijackers took off with it, but the infant is still missing.Marshall Security spokesman Kyle Van Reenen said that Netstar, SAPS and Metro Police were with the recovered car at Moody Crescent in Montclair this afternoon."There is no sign of the baby, although the vehicle has been recovered."Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said a mum, her baby and 8-year-old son were seated in their white Toyota Yaris when two armed men armed approached them."They demanded the car keys and fled with their vehicle and one-month-old baby inside. A case of carjacking has been opened at Durban Central. The baby is still missing."&nbsp;http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/hijacked-vehicle-recovered-one-month-old-baby-still-missing-20170310